citation book\">Husick, Charles B. (2009). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=S4FwbS8StvEC&amp;pg=PA50&amp;dq=definition+nautical+course&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwio64CswePSAhVF5oMKHWjlAjAQ6AEIGjAA#v=onepage&amp;q=definition%20nautical%20course&amp;f=false\"><i>Chapman Piloting, Seamanship and Small Boat Handling</i></a>. Sterling Publishing Company, Inc. p.&#160;927. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781588167446\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9781588167446\">9781588167446</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Chapman+Piloting%2C+Seamanship+and+Small+Boat+Handling&amp;rft.pages=927&amp;rft.pub=Sterling+Publishing+Company%2C+Inc.&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft.isbn=9781588167446&amp;rft.aulast=Husick&amp;rft.aufirst=Charles+B.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DS4FwbS8StvEC%26pg%3DPA50%26dq%3Ddefinition%2Bnautical%2Bcourse%26hl%3Den%26sa%3DX%26ved%3D0ahUKEwio64CswePSAhVF5oMKHWjlAjAQ6AEIGjAA%23v%3Donepage%26q%3Ddefinition%2520nautical%2520course%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACourse+%28navigation%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-AIM-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-AIM_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation book\"><a href=\"/wiki/Federal_Aviation_Administration\" title=\"Federal Aviation Administration\">Federal Aviation Administration</a> (2016). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=x8jMDAAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PT3089&amp;dq=FAA+navigation+definition+course&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjkpY_PzePSAhVK_4MKHUW7ClgQ6AEIJjAC#v=onepage&amp;q=course&amp;f=false\"><i>FAR/AIM 2017</i></a>. Skyhorse Publishing, Inc. p.&#160;1340. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781510713208\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9781510713208\">9781510713208</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=FAR%2FAIM+2017&amp;rft.pages=1340&amp;rft.pub=Skyhorse+Publishing%2C+Inc.&amp;rft.date=2016&amp;rft.isbn=9781510713208&amp;rft.au=Federal+Aviation+Administration&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Dx8jMDAAAQBAJ%26pg%3DPT3089%26dq%3DFAA%2Bnavigation%2Bdefinition%2Bcourse%26hl%3Den%26sa%3DX%26ved%3D0ahUKEwjkpY_PzePSAhVK_4MKHUW7ClgQ6AEIJjAC%23v%3Donepage%26q%3Dcourse%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACourse+%28navigation%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Nolan2010-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Nolan2010_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Michael Nolan (28 January 2010). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=6yhTiGC3ulcC&amp;pg=PA201\"><i>Fundamentals of Air Traffic Control</i></a>. Cengage Learning. p.&#160;201. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-4354-8272-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1-4354-8272-7\">1-4354-8272-7</a>. <q>For example, a runway heading north would have a magnetic heading of 360\u00b0.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Fundamentals+of+Air+Traffic+Control&amp;rft.pages=201&amp;rft.pub=Cengage+Learning&amp;rft.date=2010-01-28&amp;rft.isbn=1-4354-8272-7&amp;rft.au=Michael+Nolan&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D6yhTiGC3ulcC%26pg%3DPA201&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACourse+%28navigation%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.airliners.net/aviation-forums/tech_ops/read.main/144883/\">\"North: Zero Or Three Sixty Degrees?\"</a>. <i>airliners.net</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">6 May</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=airliners.net&amp;rft.atitle=North%3A+Zero+Or+Three+Sixty+Degrees%3F&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.airliners.net%2Faviation-forums%2Ftech_ops%2Fread.main%2F144883%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACourse+%28navigation%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">To increase readability of the diagram, all possible influences were given as positive values, e.g. variation to the east, positive deviation, wind and current from <a href=\"/wiki/Port_(nautical)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Port (nautical)\">port side</a>. The principle is the same regardless of the sign/direction of any of the components.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The \"heading and track\" diagram above shows a <a href=\"/wiki/Magnetic_declination\" title=\"Magnetic declination\">magnetic declination</a> to the east, as is commonly encountered in most of the <a href=\"/wiki/Pacific_Ocean\" title=\"Pacific Ocean\">Pacific Ocean</a>, and a somewhat exaggerated (relative to most real-life examples) deviation (of about 10\u00b0).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">By conventional <a href=\"/wiki/Degaussing\" title=\"Degaussing\">degaussing</a>, deviation could usually be kept below 10\u00b0, and <a href=\"/wiki/Fluxgate_compass\" title=\"Fluxgate compass\">fluxgate compasses</a> can be degaussed to close to 0\u00b0.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Course_(navigation)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.faa.gov/regulations_policies/handbooks_manuals/aviation/phak/\">Pilot's Handbook of Aeronautical Knowledge</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.faa.gov/regulations_policies/handbooks_manuals/aviation/phak/media/21_phak_glossary.pdf\">glossary</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1254\nCached time: 20180906224032\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.156 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.210 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 461/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 17388/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 93/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 1/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 8505/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.053/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 2.98 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  146.750      1 -total\n 51.52%   75.611      1 Template:Reflist\n 30.91%   45.359 